I love playing monk, this is my main and I don't have twink gear like Fungi and COF, all I own I made with my monk.<br>
<br>
So why did I create a monk?  Because they are fun to play!  I can still solo at 53, and I'm still useful groups. I love the fact I can FD when a fight is not in my favor, and having a mend that I can use often enough to rely on it in combat. If I see a high cliff, wall, tower or spire, I can't resist to jump down. Exception is Hole, NK and DL spires <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I don't want to lead people cross DL, they take damage just looking at a cliff.<br>
<br>
Sure, some classes might be better at solo, some more popular in groups, some might outdamage me, and some might outlive me, but who cares? I don't. I enjoy playing monk, that's what matters.<br>
<br>
After patch I could still solo my regular foes, perhaps I need 1-2 bandages more than before, but nerf wasn't as horrid as I first feared.<br>
